title: For Sale:  BA50 Match BA-50 BA 50 extremely accurate Bushmaster best 50 BMG
location: Salt Lake City, Salt Lake City, Utah
postcontent:
I have for sale my most favorite rifle. By far the most fun to shoot and the most accurate at distance of any big bore I have shot. Bushmaster used to have it guaranteed as 1 MOA accurate on their site. Perhaps with the new model they have taken that away. The good news is this model came with that guarantee! Out fitted with a 30" match grade Lothar Walther free floated barrel. This rifle will send those massive 650 grain bullets as accurately as you can. Even more accurate with the match bullets ie 750 grain Amax, Bore Riders etc. 

      I have successfully engaged targets out to 1,800 yards, that's just over a mile to the lay man. As pictured; that is 3 of 5 shots on a folding chair, yes at a mile. The other 2 weren't what you would call "flyers" they were just off the chair on the rock the chair was braced against. The rock is quite large and very impractical to fit in my vehicle to bring home to show off the group. To note that type of shooting with this rifle is the norm, not the exception. As long as you, as the shooter, are doing everything you can this rifle will perform exceptionally. 

       I have fired exactly 123 rounds of pure joy with this rifle. Each shot was a slow methodical calculation. No barrel burnouts on this one. The bore is like new with the exception that now it is broken in.... Trust me there is a lot of copper to get out with a 50 BMG on a new barrel. As the new owner you won't have to go through all that.
The main features that drew me to this rifle were; it is magazine fed, match grade free floated barrel, LEFT HAND BOLT RIGHT HAND EJECTION (more on that in a minute), being a bolt action vs a semi auto.
	The magazine fed feature speaks for itself. Multiple rounds down range with minimal time. 

---Match grade barrel for ultimate accuracy at any distance. 

---Left hand bolt-right hand ejection means the following. If you are RIGHT handed, which I am, you keep your firing hand on the grip/trigger- without breaking your firing position you reach up with your left hand to manipulate the bolt to extract the spent case and feed the next round. The entire time you can be watching the target through the optic to mark changes in shooting conditions. Extremely valuable. In fact many serious competition shooters have their rifles built this way to get as many rounds down range without breaking position and being able to watch the conditions the entire time. 

---Bolt action vs semi auto means there is the inherent safety with a bolt action rifle vs a semi auto. Does that mean that bolt actions are infallible? Of course not. Just MORE safe. 
With the extreme pressures and sheer mass of the 50 BMG cartridge, to me safety is paramount. 

	I put serious thought into which 50 BMG I wanted and it easily came down to this rifle. I have tried out a few different optics on this rifle and currently have a Sightron SIII 20x42 mounted on Burris tactical rings. Before that I had a Nightforce Benchrest 12-42x56, before that a Bushnell Tactical 10x42. The 10x was ok out to 1,000 yards.   The Nightforce just didn‚Äôt have enough travel to reach a mile even with a 20 MOA Nightforce mount and 10 MOA rail. The Sightron has an extremely impressive 150 MOA of elevation to get well beyond 2000 yards with the 50 BMG cartridge. Without holdover. It is currently dialed for 1,800 yards with a 5 mph wind left to right (last conditions I shot in).

	The rifle comes with everything pictured in the case and of course that massive case itself. The rifle, 2 10 round magazines, the factory bipod (I have installed a standard bipod stud as well), I took the forward rail off but the screws and rail are still in the case if you want it on there. 

No ammo is included at the list price. I have some available. Which will be shipped separately. 	

As the price sits the optic and rings are not included. If you want them add $500 USD.
Shipping will be actual costs via UPS to your location. 
Payment via certified funds only; cashier‚Äôs check, USPS money order, or cash face to face. 

Rifle will ship 5 business days after payment received to clear the bank.

I have the rifle listed elsewhere and reserve the right to take down the listing if it is not sold here first. 
Thank you for looking and feel free to email or call with any questions.

REDACTED
REDACTED

-Trevor

title: For Sale:  GI style Holster 45 Autos 1911 Pistols New India Dark Brown Leather WWI WWII type GL1101 Colt Government Model 45 Automatic
postcontent: Seller Stock #: GL1101 This listing is for One holster; buyers, however, may take any number of extras we have on hand at the same per-holster price, and with no additional shipping charges. Here is a very nice replica of the U.S. Army issued holsters for John Moses Browning‚Äôs 1911A1 pistol that went into service in World War I, and has now continued to protect and serve our country for more than a century. Photo specimens and their identical mates are some we found in an old Appalachian Warehouse recently. Manufacturer is Surya Company of Dehradun, Republic of India. This holster will fit any 1911 type pistol whose barrel measures 5 inches or shorter; and that includes everything from Armscors to Colts to Umarex .22 copies to Wilson Combat pistols. Our Cousin Ernest from Mississippi even carries his Ruger 22/45 in one of the old originals. Like any new, real leather holster, the first two weeks will be a very tight fit. If that weren‚Äôt the case, leather holsters would get too loose too quickly. Construction is .155 thick tanned Moroccan style genuine cow leather, just like the originals. This holster has more of a mahogany brown finish, whereas our #002 has a lighter, more reddish finish.
